Goods estimated at about N50 million have been razed by fire at the automobile section of the popular Jabi Motor Park of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). LEADERSHIP Sunday gathered that the fire incident, which started yesterday morning, destroyed about 10 shops and properties at the section of the motor park. Although investigation is still ongoing on the cause of the inferno, but there are insinuations that the fire outbreak was as a result of electrical spark following the restoration of power supply to the park in the morning. The fire incident was however put out by the men of the FCT Fire Service whose quick intervention saved the entire park from being engulfed by the inferno. The chairman of Jabi Auto Spare Parts Market, Maxwell Oparadike, who confirmed the incident to newsmen, commended the quick intervention of men of the FCT Fire Service for their efforts. Oparadike also appealed to individuals, corporate bodies and the Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA) to come to the assistance of the affected traders to enable them get back to their businesses.